{"id":14881726,"mediaExerciseId":"ad49deb2-d794-4661-8f50-ab9dcdf9b7a9","exerciseName":"6","chapterName":"20","chapterTitle":"Credit and Inventory Management","groupId":612459,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":701,"solutions":[{"id":6047432,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to determine the annual credit sales and the receivables turnover. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Suppose that the year has a $365$ days. Company Starset, Inc. has average collection period of $27$ days, and its average daily investment in receivables is $\\$46,300$. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Accounts receivable turnover can be determined using the following formula \n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{Accounts receivable turnover}&=\\frac{\\text{Number of days in the year}}{ \\text{Average collection period}}\\\\\n&=\\frac{365}{27}\\\\\n&=13.5185185\\\\\n&\\approx14\n\\end{align*}$$\n**Hence,  accounts receivable turnover is approximately 14 days.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The annual credit sales we will calculate in the following way\n$$\\begin{align*}\n\\text{The annual credit sales}&=\\text{Receivables turnover ratio}\\cdot \\text{Average daily investment in receivables}\\\\\n&=13.5185185\\cdot \\$46,300\\\\\n&=\\$625,907.41\n\\end{align*}$$\n**Hence, the annual credit sales is $625,907.41**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"a927944e-f2b9-4842-ad9d-6940373274dd","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null